  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To assess the feasibility and effectiveness of a program in L-IBD patients using CE targeted
      biopsies
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      We aim to know the prevalence and incidence of dysplasia and colitis-associated colorectal
      cancer in patients with longstanding colonic inflammatory bowel disease (N-IBD), in Spain and
      the usefulness of advanced endoscopy (chromoendoscopy) for the diagnosis and endoscopic
      differential diagnosis of N-IBD.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
